The paper discusses a framework for solving non-linear least squares optimization problems in computer vision and robotics, which are typically categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of sparse linear solvers, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the flexibility and ease of development of the framework, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
